};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Free Making Inferences Worksheets - Reading Comprehension | ToolCalcs"
  description={ws.description}
  type="article"
  structuredData={structuredData}
>
  <nav class="breadcrumb">
    <a href="/">Home</a> &rsaquo;
    <a href="/worksheets/">Worksheets</a> &rsaquo;
    <span>Making Inferences Worksheets</span>
  </nav>

  <h1>{ws.title}</h1>
  <p class="page-desc">{ws.description}</p>

  <div class="worksheet-box">
    <div class="config-panel">
      <h3>Settings</h3>
      <div class="config-inputs">
        <div class="config-group">
          <label for="cfgPassages">Number of Passages</label>
          <input type="number" id="cfgPassages" value="5" min="3" max="8" />
        </div>
        <div class="config-group">
          <label for="cfgLevel">Difficulty Level</label>
          <select id="cfgLevel">
            <option value="easy">Easy</option>
            <option value="medium" selected>Medium</option>
            <option value="hard">Hard</option>
          </select>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="worksheet-actions">
      <button class="ws-btn primary" id="btnGenerate">Generate New</button>
      <button class="ws-btn print" id="btnPrint">Print</button>
      <label class="toggle-label">
        <input type="checkbox" id="toggleAnswers" />
        Show Answers
      </label>
    </div>

    <div class="worksheet-content" id="worksheetContent">
      <div class="worksheet-header-print">
        <h2>Making Inferences Practice</h2>
        <div class="name-date">
          <span>Name: ___________________</span>
          <span>Date: ___________________</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-grid reading-grid" id="problemGrid"></div>
      <div class="answer-key hidden" id="answerKey">
        <h3>Answer Key</h3>
        <div class="answer-grid" id="answerGrid"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <AdUnit slot="ws-mid" format="rectangle" />

  <article class="content-section">
    <h2>What Is Making an Inference?</h2>
    <p>Making an inference means using clues from the text combined with your own knowledge and experience to figure out something the author does not state directly. Good readers make inferences constantly, whether they realize it or not. When a character in a story slams the door and stomps up the stairs, we infer that the character is angry, even though the word "angry" is never used. This skill is sometimes described as "reading between the lines."</p>
    <p>Inference is tested on every major reading assessment and is critical for understanding literature, science texts, historical documents, and everyday writing. Students who can make strong inferences comprehend more deeply, engage more fully with what they read, and perform better on open-ended questions that ask them to explain their thinking.</p>

    <h2>How to Make Inferences</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Look for clues in the text.</strong> Pay attention to details about characters' actions, dialogue, and descriptions.</li>
      <li><strong>Use what you already know.</strong> Combine text clues with your own life experience and background knowledge.</li>
      <li><strong>Ask: What is the author suggesting?</strong> Think about what the author wants you to understand without saying it outright.</li>
      <li><strong>Check your inference.</strong> A good inference is supported by evidence in the text. If you cannot point to specific clues, your inference may be a guess rather than a conclusion.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Common Types of Inference Questions</h2>
    <p>Inference questions come in many forms: "What can you conclude from this passage?" "What will most likely happen next?" "How does the character probably feel?" "What does the author imply?" All of these require the reader to go beyond what is explicitly stated and draw a logical conclusion based on available evidence.</p>
    <p>These worksheets present short passages at three difficulty levels, each followed by a multiple-choice inference question. At the easy level, the clues are straightforward and the correct inference is close to the surface. At the hard level, students must synthesize multiple pieces of evidence and consider subtler implications.</p>

    <h2>Related Worksheets</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/worksheets/reading-main-idea-worksheets/">Main Idea Worksheets</a> - Identify the central idea of reading passages.</li>
      <li><a href="/worksheets/reading-cause-effect-worksheets/">Cause and Effect Worksheets</a> - Identify causes and effects in text.</li>
      <li><a href="/worksheets/reading-vocabulary-context-worksheets/">Vocabulary in Context Worksheets</a> - Define words using context clues.</li>
    </ul>
  </article>

  <AdUnit slot="ws-bottom" format="horizontal" />
</BaseLayout>

<script is:inline>
  var selected = [];

  var passageBank = {
    easy: [
      { text: "Maria looked out the window and frowned. The sky was dark and she could hear rumbling in the distance. She grabbed her umbrella before heading out the door.", question: "What can you infer about the weather?", choices: ["A) It is sunny outside", "B) A storm is coming", "C) It is snowing", "D) Maria likes umbrellas"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The puppy wagged its tail and jumped up when it heard the front door open. It ran to the door and spun in circles, barking happily.", question: "What can you infer about the puppy?", choices: ["A) The puppy is scared", "B) The puppy is hungry", "C) The puppy is excited to see someone arriving", "D) The puppy wants to go outside"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "Jake looked at the empty cookie jar and then at his little sister. She had chocolate smudges on her face and was smiling.", question: "What can you infer happened to the cookies?", choices: ["A) Mom ate the cookies", "B) Jake ate the cookies", "C) The cookies were never baked", "D) Jake's sister ate the cookies"], answer: "D" },
      { text: "The classroom was decorated with streamers and balloons. A large cake sat on the teacher's desk, and the students were whispering excitedly.", question: "What can you infer is happening?", choices: ["A) The class is taking a test", "B) There is a party or celebration", "C) The teacher is absent", "D) It is the first day of school"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "Ben put on his helmet, knee pads, and gloves. He picked up his skateboard and headed to the park.", question: "What can you infer Ben is about to do?", choices: ["A) Play basketball", "B) Go swimming", "C) Go skateboarding at the park", "D) Ride his bicycle"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "The man walked slowly to the mailbox, checked inside, and sighed. He turned around with nothing in his hands and went back inside.", question: "What can you infer about the mail?", choices: ["A) The mailbox was full", "B) He received a package", "C) There was no mail in the mailbox", "D) He forgot his key"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "Sophie carried a stack of books to the front desk. She handed over her library card and waited for the librarian to scan each book.", question: "What can you infer Sophie is doing?", choices: ["A) Returning books to the library", "B) Buying books at a store", "C) Checking out books from the library", "D) Donating books"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "The baby rubbed her eyes and yawned three times in a row. She leaned her head against her mother's shoulder and her eyelids drooped.", question: "What can you infer about the baby?", choices: ["A) The baby is hungry", "B) The baby is sleepy", "C) The baby is sick", "D) The baby is bored"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "Tom stared at the flat tire on his bicycle. He reached into his backpack and pulled out a patch kit and a small pump.", question: "What can you infer Tom is going to do?", choices: ["A) Walk home", "B) Call for help", "C) Fix the flat tire himself", "D) Buy a new bicycle"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "Anna opened her lunchbox and wrinkled her nose. She quickly closed it and pushed it away without eating anything.", question: "What can you infer about Anna's lunch?", choices: ["A) She already ate", "B) The food smelled or looked bad", "C) She was not hungry", "D) She forgot her lunch money"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The family loaded suitcases into the car. Dad checked a map on his phone while Mom made sure all the windows in the house were closed and locked.", question: "What can you infer the family is doing?", choices: ["A) Going grocery shopping", "B) Moving to a new house", "C) Leaving on a trip", "D) Having guests over"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "Carlos finished his test early and checked his answers twice. He had a big smile on his face when he turned it in.", question: "What can you infer about how Carlos feels about the test?", choices: ["A) He thinks he did poorly", "B) He is confused by the questions", "C) He feels confident he did well", "D) He did not study"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "The bird hopped along the ground, dragging one wing behind it. It chirped softly but did not try to fly away.", question: "What can you infer about the bird?", choices: ["A) The bird is playing", "B) The bird is injured", "C) The bird is looking for food", "D) The bird is a baby learning to fly"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "Grandma put on her apron and set out flour, eggs, sugar, and butter on the kitchen counter. She preheated the oven to 350 degrees.", question: "What can you infer Grandma is about to do?", choices: ["A) Make a salad", "B) Clean the kitchen", "C) Bake something", "D) Cook soup"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "The boy sat alone on the bench during recess. He watched the other children play but did not join them. He looked down at his shoes and didn't smile.", question: "What can you infer about how the boy feels?", choices: ["A) He is happy being alone", "B) He is tired from running", "C) He feels lonely or left out", "D) He is in trouble with the teacher"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "The flowers in the garden were drooping and the soil was dry and cracked. Mrs. Chen shook her head and reached for the garden hose.", question: "What can you infer the garden needs?", choices: ["A) More sunlight", "B) Water", "C) Fertilizer", "D) New flowers"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The crowd jumped to their feet and cheered. The scoreboard changed and confetti fell from the ceiling.", question: "What can you infer just happened?", choices: ["A) The game was paused", "B) Someone scored a winning point or the team won", "C) The lights went out", "D) Halftime started"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "Leo packed his swim trunks, sunscreen, a towel, and a pair of goggles into his bag. He asked his mom if she had remembered the sandwiches.", question: "What can you infer about where Leo is going?", choices: ["A) To school", "B) To a friend's house", "C) To the beach or pool", "D) To the gym"], answer: "C" }
    ],
    medium: [
      { text: "When Marcus walked into the office Monday morning, his coworkers stopped talking and quickly looked away. A few people glanced at him with sympathetic expressions. His boss's door was closed, which was unusual.", question: "What can you infer about the situation?", choices: ["A) Marcus won an award", "B) Something negative may have happened involving Marcus that his coworkers know about", "C) It is a normal Monday morning", "D) Marcus forgot to wear his badge"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The restaurant had a line out the door even on a Tuesday evening. The parking lot was completely full, and people were waiting over an hour for a table without complaining.", question: "What can you infer about the restaurant?", choices: ["A) The food is probably very good", "B) The restaurant gives free food", "C) It is the only restaurant in town", "D) The service is very slow"], answer: "A" },
      { text: "The old woman carefully wrapped each plate in newspaper before placing it in a cardboard box. She taped labels on each box and stacked them neatly by the front door. The walls were bare where pictures had once hung.", question: "What can you infer the woman is doing?", choices: ["A) Redecorating her home", "B) Packing to move to a new place", "C) Having a garage sale", "D) Storing holiday decorations"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "Despite the team's losing record, the stands were packed for every home game. Fans wore the team colors, painted their faces, and chanted fight songs throughout each game.", question: "What can you infer about the fans?", choices: ["A) They only come for the food", "B) They are paid to attend", "C) They are loyal and dedicated supporters regardless of the team's record", "D) They think the team will win the championship"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "After the interview, the hiring manager shook David's hand firmly, smiled broadly, and said she would be in touch very soon. She walked him past the office where he would be working and introduced him to several team members.", question: "What can you infer about David's chances of getting the job?", choices: ["A) He did not get the job", "B) The interview went very well and he is likely to be hired", "C) The manager was just being polite", "D) David will need a second interview"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The cat arched its back, hissed loudly, and flattened its ears against its head. Its fur stood up along its spine as it backed into a corner of the room.", question: "What can you infer about how the cat feels?", choices: ["A) The cat is playful and excited", "B) The cat is hungry", "C) The cat feels threatened or frightened", "D) The cat is sleepy"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "The student's essay was covered in red ink. Almost every paragraph had comments in the margins, and several sentences were underlined with question marks beside them.", question: "What can you infer about the essay?", choices: ["A) The teacher loved the essay", "B) The essay needed significant revisions", "C) The student got an A", "D) The teacher ran out of blue ink"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "Every evening, Mr. Park walked the same route through the neighborhood. He always carried a bag of treats and knew the name of every dog on the street. The dogs would run to the fence wagging their tails when they saw him coming.", question: "What can you infer about Mr. Park?", choices: ["A) He is a dog trainer", "B) He is afraid of dogs", "C) He is a friendly, caring person who loves animals", "D) He is looking for a lost dog"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "The scientist checked the results three times, then called her colleagues over to look. Her hands were shaking slightly, and she kept saying, 'I can't believe it.' The data showed something no one had predicted.", question: "What can you infer about the results?", choices: ["A) The experiment failed", "B) The results were expected and boring", "C) The scientist made a surprising or groundbreaking discovery", "D) The data was incorrect"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "The normally busy highway had almost no traffic on it. Every shop and business along the main road was closed with lights off. The streets were quiet except for a few families walking together in their best clothes.", question: "What can you infer about the day?", choices: ["A) There is a power outage", "B) It is likely a holiday", "C) The town is being evacuated", "D) It is very early morning"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "Chen looked at the price tag on the jacket and slowly put it back on the rack. She glanced at it one more time before walking toward the clearance section at the back of the store.", question: "What can you infer about Chen?", choices: ["A) She does not like the jacket", "B) The jacket is too expensive for her budget", "C) She already has a similar jacket", "D) The store is closing"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The shelves at the grocery store were nearly empty. Shopping carts were piled high, and people were buying cases of water and canned food. The local news was running continuous weather updates.", question: "What can you infer is happening?", choices: ["A) A holiday sale is happening", "B) The store is going out of business", "C) People are preparing for a severe storm or natural disaster", "D) There is a food shortage"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "The musician played the same four bars of music over and over, each time slightly differently. She paused, scribbled notes on paper, crossed some out, and played again. A wastebasket beside the piano was overflowing with crumpled paper.", question: "What can you infer the musician is doing?", choices: ["A) Performing a concert", "B) Composing or perfecting a piece of music", "C) Practicing for a recital", "D) Teaching a student"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The new employee arrived thirty minutes early every day, stayed late without being asked, and volunteered for every extra project. Within six months, she had been promoted twice.", question: "What can you infer about the employee?", choices: ["A) She had connections at the company", "B) She was overpaid", "C) Her hard work and initiative led to her rapid promotion", "D) The company promoted everyone quickly"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "The trail was steep and rocky, and the hikers stopped frequently to catch their breath. Their water bottles were nearly empty, and the summit was still nowhere in sight. Despite this, none of them suggested turning back.", question: "What can you infer about the hikers?", choices: ["A) They are lost", "B) They are experienced professionals", "C) They are determined to reach the summit despite the difficulty", "D) They have plenty of supplies"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "At the school science fair, one project had a large crowd gathered around it while most other tables had only the judges stopping by. Students from other schools were taking photos of the display and asking the presenter questions.", question: "What can you infer about this science project?", choices: ["A) It is the worst project at the fair", "B) It is particularly impressive or interesting", "C) The student's parents are there", "D) The project is about a popular topic"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The doctor looked at the test results, paused, and then asked Mrs. Rivera to sit down. He spoke in a calm, careful voice and asked if she had someone who could drive her home.", question: "What can you infer about the test results?", choices: ["A) The results are normal", "B) The results likely contain bad or serious news", "C) The doctor made an error", "D) Mrs. Rivera needs more tests"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The garden that had been neglected for years was now full of color. Fresh mulch lined the paths, new flowers bloomed in neat rows, and a small fountain bubbled in the center. A woman in gardening gloves stood back and admired her work with satisfaction.", question: "What can you infer about the woman?", choices: ["A) She hired someone to fix the garden", "B) She personally restored the neglected garden", "C) She just moved into the house", "D) The garden grows by itself"], answer: "B" }
    ],
    hard: [
      { text: "The CEO's resignation letter praised the company and expressed gratitude, but it was notably brief and lacked any mention of future plans. The board's official statement thanked her for her service but did not include the customary phrase about wishing her well in future endeavors. Stock prices dipped immediately after the announcement.", question: "What can you infer about the circumstances of the resignation?", choices: ["A) The CEO retired happily after a long career", "B) The resignation was likely forced or under contentious circumstances", "C) The CEO is starting her own company", "D) The board was surprised by the resignation"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The ambassador's speech at the United Nations was unusually short. She read directly from prepared remarks without making eye contact with the audience and left immediately afterward without taking questions from reporters, which was unlike her usual open and engaging style.", question: "What can you infer about the ambassador?", choices: ["A) She was running late for another meeting", "B) She may be delivering a message she does not personally agree with or is under political pressure", "C) She was not prepared for the speech", "D) The speech was unimportant"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The bookstore on the corner had been there for forty years. Last month, the owner began selling furniture and shelving along with the remaining books at steep discounts. The landlord was seen showing the empty space to people in business suits.", question: "What can you infer is happening to the bookstore?", choices: ["A) The bookstore is expanding", "B) The owner is remodeling", "C) The bookstore is closing permanently", "D) The landlord is buying more books"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "The student council president gave a speech calling for better cafeteria food and longer lunch periods. The principal sat in the back row with her arms crossed, and her expression did not change throughout the speech. Afterward, she walked out without applauding.", question: "What can you infer about the principal's reaction?", choices: ["A) She fully supports the student's proposals", "B) She is indifferent to the speech", "C) She likely disagrees with or disapproves of the proposals", "D) She did not hear the speech"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "The painting had been attributed to an unknown artist for decades. When a restorer carefully cleaned a corner of the canvas, she discovered a signature hidden under layers of varnish. She immediately stopped work and called the museum director, her voice trembling with excitement.", question: "What can you infer about the hidden signature?", choices: ["A) The signature is illegible", "B) It likely belongs to a famous or significant artist, making the painting much more valuable", "C) The restorer made a mistake", "D) The museum knew about the signature all along"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "During the debate, the candidate answered every question about the economy with detailed statistics and confident body language. However, when asked about her environmental record, she paused for several seconds, repeated the question back, and then pivoted to talking about job creation instead.", question: "What can you infer about the candidate's environmental record?", choices: ["A) She has a strong environmental record", "B) She did not understand the question", "C) Her environmental record may be weak or politically unfavorable, so she avoided the topic", "D) She thinks the economy is more important"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "The novelist's latest book was released to enormous publicity and sold millions of copies in its first week. Critics, however, noted that it closely followed the exact formula of his previous five bestsellers: same character archetypes, same plot structure, same resolution. Sales remained strong despite the lukewarm reviews.", question: "What can you infer about the novelist's approach?", choices: ["A) He is a literary innovator", "B) He prioritizes commercial success over creative risk-taking", "C) Critics always dislike popular books", "D) The publisher forced him to write the same story"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The refugees arrived at the border carrying nothing but the clothes they wore. Children clung to their parents, many of whom stared ahead with blank expressions. Aid workers noted that the group had walked for over two hundred miles and that many had untreated injuries.", question: "What can you infer about the conditions the refugees fled?", choices: ["A) They left voluntarily for better jobs", "B) They were on a planned vacation", "C) They fled desperate and likely dangerous conditions with no time to prepare", "D) The border was nearby their homes"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "The email from the head of HR invited all employees to a mandatory meeting on Friday afternoon. No agenda was provided, and managers were told not to discuss the meeting in advance. The company had reported declining revenue for three consecutive quarters.", question: "What can you infer about the purpose of the meeting?", choices: ["A) A company party is being planned", "B) Layoffs, restructuring, or other significant bad news will likely be announced", "C) Employees will receive bonuses", "D) The meeting is a routine check-in"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The teenager had been saving money for months, cutting lawns and walking dogs after school. He kept a picture of a red car torn from a magazine taped to his bedroom wall. On his sixteenth birthday, he counted his savings and frowned, then went back to his phone to look for more lawn care jobs.", question: "What can you infer?", choices: ["A) He does not really want the car", "B) He has saved enough money", "C) He has not yet saved enough to buy the car and is determined to keep working", "D) His parents are buying him the car"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "The museum exhibit on climate change had been open for three months. Visitor surveys showed high satisfaction, and school groups filled the calendar. However, two corporate sponsors quietly withdrew their funding, and the museum director received several critical letters from industry groups.", question: "What can you infer about the controversy?", choices: ["A) The exhibit is unpopular with the public", "B) Corporate sponsors may disagree with the exhibit's message and pressured the museum", "C) The museum is running out of money", "D) School groups complained about the content"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The retired professor kept every letter her former students had ever sent her, organized in boxes by decade. She reread them each year on the anniversary of her retirement. When asked about her career, she did not mention her publications or awards but instead named individual students and what they were doing now.", question: "What can you infer about what the professor values most?", choices: ["A) Her academic publications", "B) Her awards and recognition", "C) Her relationships with students and their success", "D) Her retirement"], answer: "C" },
      { text: "The politician voted in favor of the bill publicly but told reporters he had serious reservations about several provisions. His chief of staff later leaked that the vote was part of an agreement with party leadership in exchange for support on a different bill the politician cared about more.", question: "What can you infer about the politician's vote?", choices: ["A) He genuinely supported the bill", "B) His vote was strategic rather than based on conviction about this particular bill", "C) He was confused about the bill's contents", "D) Party leadership forced him to vote against his will"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The town had celebrated the annual harvest festival for over a century. This year, the organizing committee received three times the usual number of vendor applications but half the usual number of volunteer sign-ups. The committee chair sent an urgent email to local civic groups asking for help.", question: "What can you infer about the festival's situation?", choices: ["A) The festival has too many volunteers", "B) Interest from vendors is strong but there are not enough volunteers to run the event", "C) The festival is being canceled", "D) The committee does not want more vendors"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The child prodigy performed flawlessly at the concert, earning a standing ovation from the audience. Backstage, however, her parents noticed she had bitten her nails down to nothing, and her tutor mentioned she had been sleeping poorly and refusing to eat before performances.", question: "What can you infer about the child?", choices: ["A) She loves performing and is perfectly happy", "B) The pressure of performing is causing her significant stress and anxiety", "C) She is physically ill with an unrelated condition", "D) Her parents are proud and she feels supported"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The two countries signed a trade agreement with great ceremony, but the fine print included provisions that would not take effect for ten years and could be renegotiated at any time by either party. Economists noted that the agreement contained no enforcement mechanisms.", question: "What can you infer about the trade agreement?", choices: ["A) It will immediately boost trade between the two countries", "B) It is more symbolic than practically binding", "C) Both countries are fully committed to its terms", "D) Economists are impressed by its strength"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "After the forest fire, the blackened landscape looked lifeless. But within weeks, bright green shoots began pushing through the ash. Biologists explained that certain plant species have seeds that only germinate after exposure to intense heat, and that the fire had cleared away dense undergrowth that had been blocking sunlight from the forest floor.", question: "What can you infer about the role of fire in this ecosystem?", choices: ["A) Fire is purely destructive and the forest will never recover", "B) Fire plays a natural role in forest renewal by triggering germination and clearing undergrowth", "C) The biologists planted new seeds after the fire", "D) The forest was already dying before the fire"], answer: "B" },
      { text: "The app had millions of downloads and a devoted user base, but it had never turned a profit. Investors continued to pour money into the company based on growth projections, even as competitors launched similar products with lower costs. The founders spoke optimistically about future monetization strategies they had not yet implemented.", question: "What can you infer about the company's financial health?", choices: ["A) The company is financially stable", "B) The company's long-term viability is uncertain despite its popularity", "C) Investors are pulling out", "D) The founders have a proven monetization plan"], answer: "B" }
    ]
  };

  function shuffle(arr) {
    for (var i = arr.length - 1; i > 0; i--) {
      var j = Math.floor(Math.random() * (i + 1));
      var temp = arr[i]; arr[i] = arr[j]; arr[j] = temp;
    }
    return arr;
  }

  function generateProblems() {
    var count = parseInt(document.getElementById('cfgPassages').value, 10);
    var level = document.getElementById('cfgLevel').value;

    if (isNaN(count) || count < 3) count = 3;
    if (count > 8) count = 8;

    var pool = passageBank[level].slice();
    shuffle(pool);
    selected = pool.slice(0, Math.min(count, pool.length));

    renderProblems();
    renderAnswerKey();
    updateAnswerVisibility();
  }

  function renderProblems() {
    var grid = document.getElementById('problemGrid');
    var showAnswers = document.getElementById('toggleAnswers').checked;
    var html = '';

    for (var i = 0; i < selected.length; i++) {
      var p = selected[i];
      html += '<div class="reading-passage">';
      html += '<div class="problem-number">' + (i + 1) + ')</div>';
      html += '<div class="passage-text">' + p.text + '</div>';
      html += '<div class="passage-question"><strong>' + p.question + '</strong></div>';
      html += '<div class="passage-choices">';
      for (var j = 0; j < p.choices.length; j++) {
        var isCorrect = showAnswers && p.choices[j].charAt(0) === p.answer;
        html += '<div class="choice' + (isCorrect ? ' correct' : '') + '">' + p.choices[j] + '</div>';
      }
      html += '</div>';
      html += '</div>';
    }

    grid.innerHTML = html;
  }

  function renderAnswerKey() {
    var answerGrid = document.getElementById('answerGrid');
    var html = '';
    for (var i = 0; i < selected.length; i++) {
      html += '<div class="answer-item">';
      html += '<span class="q">' + (i + 1) + '.</span>';
      html += '<span class="a">' + selected[i].answer + '</span>';
      html += '</div>';
    }
    answerGrid.innerHTML = html;
  }

  function updateAnswerVisibility() {
    var showAnswers = document.getElementById('toggleAnswers').checked;
    var answerKey = document.getElementById('answerKey');
    if (showAnswers) { answerKey.classList.remove('hidden'); }
    else { answerKey.classList.add('hidden'); }
    renderProblems();
  }

  document.getElementById('btnGenerate').addEventListener('click', generateProblems);
  document.getElementById('btnPrint').addEventListener('click', function () { window.print(); });
  document.getElementById('toggleAnswers').addEventListener('change', updateAnswerVisibility);
  generateProblems();
</script>
